## Scope & Method

## Consolidation Targets

- Household types: consolidate `Household`, `HouseholdMember`, `HouseholdRecord`, `HouseholdWithMembersResult` in `src/types/households.ts` and import from there.
  - Keep `HouseholdFormData` canonical in `src/types/forms.ts` (re-export from `src/types/households.ts` already exists).
- Auth types: consolidate `UserProfile`, `PaginationParams` (auth-related), and `CSRFToken` under `src/types/auth.ts`.
  - For CSRF helpers, centralize token creators in `src/lib/authentication/csrf.ts` and import where needed.
- Address types: consolidate `AddressLabels`, `AddressDisplayInfo` in `src/types/addresses.ts` and reference from services and utils.
- Chart types: consolidate `PieSliceData`, `PieSliceWithAngles`, `ChartDataPoint` in `src/types/charts.ts` and re-use in chart utilities/components.
- Cache types: consolidate `CacheEntry`, `CacheStats` in `src/types/services.ts` and import into `src/lib/data/*` and `src/services/*`.
- Error/API types: consolidate `DatabaseResponse` and related error types in `src/types/errors.ts`; prefer re-exports over redefining in auth error files.
- Repository helpers: replace repeated `queryBuilder` implementations in repositories with a shared helper in `src/services/base-repository.ts` (or a small `src/services/repository-utils.ts`) and import it in each repository.
- Validation/sanitization: consolidate `sanitizeSearchQuery` and related helpers in `src/lib/validation/sanitizers.ts`; update other modules to import from there.
- UI handlers: duplicates like `handleChange`, `handleSubmit`, `handleKeyDown` are per-component by design and typically should remain localized; no consolidation recommended.
- Next.js route handlers: `GET`/`POST` duplicates are expected (one per route file); keep as-is.
